The paper discusses efficient constructions and algorithms for various problems, such as acyclic edge coloring and non-repetitive graph colorings, which fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of the Lovasz Local Lemma in graph theory (cs.GT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the randomness of the output distribution of the Moser-Tardos procedure, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the running time of the Moser-Tardos algorithm, which is a computational complexity issue and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
